    "updated_at": "2015-08-27T17:13:17Z",
    "body": "The delimiter is emitted so that tuples and other composites don't offer easy ways to get hash collisions. It makes sense that the hashing algorithm should be able to decide how to handle these, especially since the faster hashers may not care about preventing hash flooding. SipHasher will of course continue to _care_.\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
