    "body": "@pczarn The main target is a speedup where hashing needs only a single write, the rest is a bonus. I consider this change to only be the next best thing after some kind of explicit one-shot hashing, but it seems hard to implement that in a backwards compatible way.\n\nI don't think hash with seed is that bad, it's using a function I didn't profile really either, maybe it can be improved. We can skip the seed on the first invocation of write.\n",
