    "created_at": "2015-09-16T14:46:36Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-16T14:46:36Z",
    "body": "I like the idea of catering to algorithms like Farmhash, but this method seems a little odd to add for cases like that. Do you know if other hashing frameworks typically have methods like this?\n\nOne thing I'd be worried about is what happens if you call `delimit` but then don't write any data? I think, however, it'd be fine to just clearly document that it's an erroneous case that's not guaranteed to work.\n",
