    "created_at": "2015-09-16T15:57:10Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-16T15:57:10Z",
    "body": "@alexcrichton That ought to be a valid operation. Hashing `(\"\", \"x\", \"\")` will end up doing that. As you can see, without the elision of delimiters, the slice hashing is just the same as before. We could even choose to not elide any delimiters for Siphash at all.\n\nThis PR is just experimental, I'd want to do something like gankro's hash_one_shot idea, but I can't find a way to do it that doesn't also change Hash / Hasher backwards incompatibly.\n\nThe main thing I'm worried is that someone will point out how chunking-dependent hashing might totally break hashing of some types (I can imagine a rope behaving that way). Should that stop this proposal, even if this proposal doesn't introduces that, it only _caters_ to a farmhash impl that could do so?\n",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
